Pour 300ml cold @water{300%ml} into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover and cook for ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the #pot{} from the heat. Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @mushrooms{150%g}. Halve the @chilli{1} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Stir the @coconut milk{1%pack} (or shake the packet) to dissolve any lumps.

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. When the pan is hot, add the onion, @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g} and mushrooms. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Fry until browned, stirring occasionally, ~{5-6%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Add the @garlic, ginger & lemongrass paste{1%sachet} and chilli (use less if you don't like spice). Fry until fragrant, another ~{30%seconds}. Add coconut milk and 25ml water to the pan. Cover and cook for ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Loosen the sauce with a splash of water if necessary. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

While the chicken cooks, trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}. Add the @honey{2%sachets} and @miso paste{1%sachet} to a #bowl{} and mix to combine.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between #bowls{}. Top with the fragrant chicken curry. Drizzle the honey miso sauce over the chicken. Finish with a sprinkling of sliced scallion.